captions.text: - Well hello, everyone.
My name is Tyler Oakley,
and today I just wanna chill with you.
It's a new year, happy New Year!
I hope you guys had a fun new year.
I hope you had a fresh new year.
A fantastic new year.
A f-f-f-fun fabulous time.

I hope you had a good
time, I hope it was safe.

I hope you didn't get
so drunk that you were
so terribly hung over the next day.

I hope that you kissed
somebody consenually
that you wanted to kiss.

I hope that you were okay
with it, if you didn't
kiss anybody because your worth is not
based on whether or not you touched
somebody else's lips with your lips.
I just want you to know that.
That's all I want you to know.
I hope you had a fabulous New Years
and the holiday season before then.
I am back in L.A.
I was in Australia for New Years
and I am back in L.A.
I am really actually happy to be back

because the last couple
months I've been like
on the go, and I just have been
going, going, going, going, going
because I am a workaholic sometimes
and I just work and work and work and work

and work and work and you
guys see that all the time.
You guys are always really nice to me.
Like, "Take some time, Tyler, stop.
"Go home, sleep in your own bed."
And I'm like, "Okay, maybe later."

Right now is when I've
been kind of doing that.

As you guys know I didn't
put up a video on Tuesday
and I didn't put up a video on Friday,
but I'm uploading this because I wanted
to just say hey.

I wanna make videos when
I wanna make videos.
After seven years of doing it,
I'm to the point where maybe sometimes

I'll stick to a schedule,
sometimes I won't.

And sometimes I'll have
stuff to talk about
and sometimes I won't.
And sometimes I'll do fun things
and sometimes I won't.

Maybe I'll upload this
without a single edit.
Wouldn't that be crazy?

(singing) Wouldn't it be
nice, deh, deh, deh, deh.

See, I could sing, and
I'm not gonna edit it out
because I'm not editing this video.

Unless I do edit it, and then
I'll edit that part out, too.

Anyway, I hope you had a
fabulous holiday season.
I hope you had a fabulous New Years.
I hope that you are relaxing a little bit
or maybe you just went back to school.
Sorry if you did, sucks to suck,

but education is great,
I hope you graduate.
What a song!
And I hope you actually go off to college.
Or don't, if it's not your thing.
Anyway, where am I going with this?
I am back in L.A., I am a bit recharged.
Like I said, I went to Australia

for a little bit of holiday,
a little bit of work

because I was working
like a live stream thing
for New Years on the countdown.
I'm back in L.A. and I spent the weeks
just like chillin', relaxing.
I have been working on projects
that you guys don't know about yet,
so stick around for that.

This year has been so
far really refreshing
and I feel like I've been really honest
with myself and I've been processing a lot

of things that I've
been meaning to process
for years and years and years.
So that's a cool thing.
You'll know about a lot of that stuff soon
because I've been working on some stuff.
Don't you hate it when YouTubers are like,
"I'm workin' on stuff," and I'm like,
"Cool, nobody gives a shit."
There's no glory in the process.
Give us what you're workin' on
or keep it to yourself.

I'm being that asshole
right now, so sorry.
But yeah, cool stuff is comin'.
Again, no glory in the process.
I keep reminding myself of that.
I have a sticky note on my desk
that says "No glory in the process."
I think that's a good reminder of like,
you know what, just because you mean

to do something, and maybe
this is about like resolutions.

Maybe because you mean to
do something, that's cool.

But it doesn't mean shit
unless you actually do it.

And that's what I think "no
glory in the process" means.
You can take your own interpretation.

I saw a sticky note of
that quote on somebody

that I work with on her
desk and I was like,
"Damn, that's good."
So I've been kind of keeping that in mind

with projects that I'm
doing and not wanting
to gloat about them or brag about them

or talk about how I'm
workin' on them all the time
'cause it's like it doesn't matter
until the results are out there

and people can still
enjoy what you worked on,
the project in its fully glory.
So yeah, no glory in the process.
Stick around, you're not gonna hear about
those big things much because those things
aren't out yet, and when they are out,
then you'll hear about 'em.

But yeah, I hope you guys
are having a good life.
I hope January is treatin' ya good.
2015, how'd that happen?
Who knows?

But I think this year's
gonna be really good.
If you didn't see, I uploaded a video

that was like a hundred
things and I did it in 2014.
I did it in 2013's year,
a hundred things I did in 2013
and then I did it again for 2014.
Every time I upload one of those videos

it's really daunting and
actually kind of stressful

because seeing everything
that I did last year

I'm like how am I ever going
to top last year this year?

I felt the same way at
the beginning of last year
when I uploaded the previous year's video.

I just have to remember
that you know what,
I am just here to live my best life.
This thing that we're doing right now,
my YouTube channel, is just a platform
for me to have a diary.
I should not feel like I have to fill
any expectations of outdoing myself.

I think the most important
thing is having fun
and enjoying what I make and you guys

being somewhat entertained
and enjoying the diary.
Because like I said, I've always said
this is just a diary.
At the end of the day I have nothing else
but memory for me to look back on,
then that's cool.
And maybe someday my kids will watch this
and see what I was up to in January 2015
and maybe their kids might see that,
and who knowssssss?
Cool video, Tyler.
Never claimed it was gonna be!

If you like this video, be
sure to give it a thumbs up
and subscribe.

You know, there's a lot of
expectations people have.
Just because somebody has a certain amount
of subscribers doesn't mean they can just
not sit down and chat with people.

That's why I'm on
YouTube, just to connect.

And if you want to
connect with me this year,

stick around, subscribe,
give this video a thumbs up.

If you wanna see my latest
video, click right there.

If you wanna see my latest
podcast, click right there.
Not see it, hear it.
It's all about 2015 predictions.

It was really funny, I
had a lot of fun with it.
And if you wanna be my person of the week,
click right there.

And yeah, that's all I
have for you guys today.
I hope you have a fabulous life
and I will see you guys next time.
Okay, byeeee (making baby noises)
Honestly, to just sit down it feels kinda good.
So I hope you guys didn't mind that, ummm yeah.
I love you.
That's all.
Okay.
Cool. (giggle)
Bye.
